Derrick Spies, Correspondent (Wilderness search and rescue) 
	        Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories
	     Cape Town – The body of a 57-year-old man was recovered from Chapman’s Peak on Friday afternoon. Police spokesperson, Captain FC van Wyk, said the man’s body had been found at Chapman’s Drive on Friday afternoon by his wife. Van Wyk said that an inquest docket had been opened. Voluntary organisation Wilderness Search and Rescue (WSAR) spokesperson Johann Johann Marais, said they had been approached by the police to assist in recovering the body as it was fairly inaccessible area. Marais said they had begun operations at around 15:30, and the body had been recovered by 17:30. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  